"I used to be an egolifter and threw big weights around with bad form, but then I watched Mike Israel and started doing everything slow and controlled just like he told me. It really humbles you and crushes your ego. Struggling to bench a plate shows you how weak you really are."

"It's very humbling to go from curling the 75s for reps to the 20s, but the squeeze is crazy when you control the eccentric all the way down and the pump is out of this world. You know what Dr. Israel always says: when you go to the gym, you have to leave your ego at the door..."

"Benching three plates might be impressive to others, but doing one plate with a three second controlled eccentric to failure leads to far better muscle fibre recruitment (and keeps your ego in check). Especially with Dr. Israel's caf-free Nitric Oxide blend pre-workout formula."
